{"id":"salem","term":"Salem","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Peace, commonly supposed to be another name of Jerusalem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 14:18\">Gen. 14:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 76:2\">Ps. 76:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 7:1\">Heb. 7:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 7:2\">2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 14:18","Psalms 76:2","Hebrews 7:1","Hebrews 7:2"]}